column5: Drill a hole, catch a fish. That was today's strategy. Even if the hole was a foot away. Good mixed bag, plenty released. Kept 7 perch and a crappie. No pike bites all day, besides the 38" that Rob caught and released before I got there.
Beautiful colours! Nice quality zoom on the camera. Thanks for sharing.
nicely done, looks like u had a blast... thnx for sharin
Nice piglet's!  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
white crappie?  Nice fish!  Same story up here. 1 or 2 fish per hole. Have to keep moving.
Nice going!  Hate the BEARS toque...hate the bears...go PACKERS!
Good pics. Love the clarity and the vivid colours.
nice day on the ice congrats but the hat is awesome
Now that's some good fishin, that there is!  I love the close up shots of the fish, Rich.
And a pic of the 38 inch beast Rob caught 2 hrs before I hit the ice:    :clapping:  :clapping:
Nice going! Looks like a great day on the ice.  Good to see you around here Rich....been a while hasn't it?

"Nice going! Hate the BEARS toque...hate the bears...go PACKERS!"  clinched there division,by in the first round,nuff said!! lol...  as always,it was a blast to be out catching some fish with ya,rich!!
nice job ladies  we REALLY need to get together again sometime...

I think you'd hate that experience nowadays Scott. Straight up fishing, none of that "funny business" anymore. And with the exception of this one trip (literally) we make damn sure 99% of the fish make it back down the hole.
That pike is a beauty!  And the pannies aren't bad either...way to go
Johnnyb are you the dude who was talking to Rob about me on the ice?
